content.description: Fun climbing on great, big cobbles. Use the "flake" out right. (Start a bit right of the first bolt).
content.location: Starts by a tree on the west wall (on your left as you're looking uphill in the corridor)

content.description: Climb up the low-angle start into the first overhang. Move quickly on less-than-ideal edgy hands to pull over the roof onto lower-angle terrain. Easy walk to the next roof, where you'll find some comforting jugs.
content.location: Second climb from the left on the the west wall (which is the wall on the left as you enter the area).

climbs.name: Rebar & Rakes
climbs.fa: Chris Magerl, Stefani Day, John Shields

content.description: Fun cobble climbing without much fear factor. Try to stay out of the moss, though. Near the top, head slightly right to skirt the little scoop/roof.
content.location: Starts just left of the slot/alcove, on the east wall (right wall as you enter the corridor)

content.description: Easy start on well-weathered cobbles. It gets progressively steeper and a bit thin at the top.
content.location: The farthest right route on the west wall.

climbs.name: I've Got Blisters On My Fingers!

content.description: A multiple personality climb--fun, juggy arete at the start, super low-angle middle, to a pumpy, insecure finish. BETA ALERT: a hidden pocket out left makes clipping the 6th bolt much easier. It would rate another star if not for the low-angle middle
content.location: Starts on the arete to the right of the slot/alcove

content.description: Quite vertical, but positive holds and plenty of good feet except around the 3rd bolt. A hidden pocket is a real find when you're searching for a foot.
content.location: Second climb to the left of the slot/alcove (and right of the big scoop) on the east wall (right wall as you enter the corridor)

content.description: Fun climb with three roofs spanned by much easier bits. Starts easy enough (go ahead and skip the first bolt, if you want). Clip the 3rd bolt and pull over the first roof on slopey cobbles. Cruise over the second and third roofs with much better holds. Third roof is easiest left of the bolt.
content.location: Starts at the toe of the west wall, just right of the cave. The first climb you'll come to on the Birthday Corridor trail.

content.description: Climbs to the left of the big scoop on the east wall. Easy for the first few feet, then progressively steepens. The crux is getting to the 4th bolt, which is hidden (sorry). Head up and right from bolt #3. Easier climbing gets you to the anchors.
content.location: Starts by a tree, just left of a big scoop on the east wall of the corridor (the wall on the right as you enter the area). Uphill from the rest of the climbs. A nice bench is near the belay platform.

content.description: Steep, juggy start to a super-fun lower-angle mini-arete.
content.location: Just to the right of the scoop/roof at the toe of the west wall (on your left as you enter the Corridor)

content.description: Start in the Chimney climb up and sling a chockstone,  Continue up to the top of the Chimney/OW placing a #7 then #6, and finally a#5 near the top.  From here traverse climbers left to a bolt and finish on Rebars and Rakes.
content.location: This is the obvious chimney just left of I've got blisters on my fingers.
